cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning techniques for quality estimation in machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses neural networks and transfer learning, which are common techniques in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes ensemble techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions using pre-trained models, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
